        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is given by the reference to CD’s manuscript on fowls for <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref>, which he finished in 1861. See ‘Journal’ (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 9, Appendix II).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD had asked Tegetmeier to read and make comments on the chapter on fowls that he was preparing (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3095.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to W. B. Tegetmeier, 22 March [1861]</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7656.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Tegetmeier 1861</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3108.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to W. B. Tegetmeier, 2 April [1861]</ref>. Sebright fowl were named after their breeder, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4272.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Saunders Sebright</ref> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2063.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">DNB</hi></ref>).</note>
